attributes.Long form description: The general instruction is to disassemble the furniture. The student starts by unscrewing the top table. Then the student unscrews the hex socket heads on the shelf. In the end, the student places all the parts on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Hello, and thank you for taking part in our study. In front of you, you'll see the Knarrevik Ikea nightstand.
Your task, for now, will be to disassemble it.
You may now begin, thank you.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the top shelf of the table.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student was turning the screw in the opposite direction.
The student accidentally dropped the hex socket head.
The student should hold the tray when he disassemble it.
The student should hold the hex_socket_head when he disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first leg.

attributes.Transcription: Unintelligible disassemble in the leg to the first.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the second leg.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student rotates the furniture wrongly.

attributes.Transcription: Please, rotate the face so that it is laying on one of its short ends.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student rotates the furniture wrongly.

attributes.Transcription: Please, flip the feet again. So that the pieces are oriented with the *unintelligible* feet on the left.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the third leg.
The student disassembles the fourth leg.

attributes.Transcription: That was everything for this task. You may now go ahead and press the stop button. Thank you.
